WEBVTT

00:00:11.116 --> 00:00:15.120
NOTES FROM THE LAST ROW

00:00:18.498 --> 00:00:19.749
Are you telling me

00:00:20.875 --> 00:00:22.544
to fabricate the truth?

00:00:22.627 --> 00:00:23.461
<i>What, fabricate?</i>

00:00:24.045 --> 00:00:25.171
Well, aren't you?

00:00:25.672 --> 00:00:28.716
I never followed them to the hospital
or saw anything.

00:00:29.217 --> 00:00:31.719
How could I have seen Mr. Kim
hurting Min-hui--

00:00:31.803 --> 00:00:33.138
You punk!

00:00:35.306 --> 00:00:37.809
You listen to me carefully.

00:00:38.685 --> 00:00:41.437
This isn't fabrication.

00:00:41.521 --> 00:00:44.816
This is the truth.
An undeniable truth based on all we know.

00:00:44.899 --> 00:00:46.985
Why else would Kim Su-hun
show up at the park

00:00:47.068 --> 00:00:49.487
after seeing the letter
about the CCTV footage?

00:00:49.988 --> 00:00:53.533
That was him effectively admitting
to the crime through his actions!

00:00:58.204 --> 00:01:00.748
Lee Kang. Are you still listening?

00:01:04.252 --> 00:01:06.588
Even so, I can't
write about something I didn't see.

00:01:07.088 --> 00:01:08.256
That would be lying.

00:01:09.215 --> 00:01:11.426
<i>What did you tell me time and time again?</i>

00:01:11.926 --> 00:01:14.762
<i>That a writer must be objective</i>
<i>and see reality as it is.</i>

00:01:14.846 --> 00:01:15.763
<i>Be truthful.</i>

00:01:15.847 --> 00:01:16.764
That's right!

00:01:17.265 --> 00:01:18.892
I know. I do.

00:01:19.475 --> 00:01:22.061
I'm not saying we should commit fraud.

00:01:22.645 --> 00:01:26.774
We're just filling in a small gap
in the truth with our imagination.

00:01:26.858 --> 00:01:28.902
That's what stories are all about.

00:01:28.985 --> 00:01:30.612
Fiction that strives for the truth.

00:01:30.695 --> 00:01:33.740
That's the true power of stories!

00:01:36.659 --> 00:01:37.952
<i>I don't know.</i>

00:01:39.454 --> 00:01:41.623
<i>What do you intend</i>
<i>by writing a story like that?</i>

00:01:41.706 --> 00:01:46.461
We need to expose that bastard
Kim Su-hun's true colors to the world.

00:01:48.046 --> 00:01:50.298
That's the duty of a writer
who knows the truth.

00:01:52.300 --> 00:01:53.176
No.

00:01:54.844 --> 00:01:56.054
I can't do it.

00:01:56.554 --> 00:01:59.891
Besides, I can't write anymore.
My dad's not doing well.

00:02:02.977 --> 00:02:05.688
To be honest, I had a really tough week.

00:02:06.606 --> 00:02:08.399
If you want it written, do it yourself.

00:02:09.776 --> 00:02:11.611
What? Me?

00:02:12.445 --> 00:02:13.404
How could I?

00:02:13.905 --> 00:02:15.531
You're the writer, kid!

00:02:15.615 --> 00:02:18.743
<i>Why not? You used to write before.</i>

00:02:20.245 --> 00:02:23.957
You're the writer of this story now,
so do whatever you want with it.

00:02:25.917 --> 00:02:27.001
<i>I'm sorry, Mr. Heo.</i>

00:02:27.085 --> 00:02:28.419
Hey, Lee Kang!

00:02:28.503 --> 00:02:30.338
I'm not done talking, hey!

00:02:30.421 --> 00:02:32.006
You bastard, don't hang up!

00:02:32.799 --> 00:02:35.218
You ungrateful bastard!

00:03:05.498 --> 00:03:06.457
What did he say?

00:03:11.546 --> 00:03:13.256
I'm the writer now?

00:03:43.328 --> 00:03:44.537
I'm…

00:03:45.830 --> 00:03:47.498
I'm the writer now?

00:04:00.678 --> 00:04:01.846
I'm the writer now?

00:04:07.560 --> 00:04:11.314
I couldn't really tell
what the author was trying to say.

00:04:12.523 --> 00:04:14.192
It made me think,

00:04:14.692 --> 00:04:17.195
why bother writing
when you have nothing to say?

00:04:19.280 --> 00:04:21.282
It's okay to live as is.

00:04:22.825 --> 00:04:25.078
But, above all else,

00:04:26.079 --> 00:04:28.122
you should relearn sentence structures.

00:04:40.301 --> 00:04:43.221
Watch closely, Kim Su-hun,
you son of a bitch.

00:04:45.264 --> 00:04:47.308
I'll show you.

00:06:03.176 --> 00:06:06.554
NOTES FROM THE LAST ROW
BY HEO MUN-OH

00:06:47.345 --> 00:06:48.179
Yes.

00:06:50.014 --> 00:06:51.682
It wasn't all a dream.

00:06:57.438 --> 00:07:00.107
This is my novel.

00:07:01.567 --> 00:07:02.652
This is mine.

00:07:09.659 --> 00:07:11.244
My second novel.

00:07:44.569 --> 00:07:45.945
Well, look who it is.

00:07:46.654 --> 00:07:49.156
-Well, if it isn't Mr. Newbie Writer.
-<i>Mr. Heo?</i>

00:07:49.240 --> 00:07:52.034
-Calling me early today--
-<i>Why weren't you answering?</i>

00:07:53.411 --> 00:07:55.871
You crazy bastard,
yelling at me like some…

00:07:55.955 --> 00:07:57.290
You rude little shit!

00:07:57.373 --> 00:07:59.041
<i>I've been calling you all night!</i>

00:07:59.750 --> 00:08:00.668
What?

00:08:03.170 --> 00:08:05.006
LEE KANG
13 MISSED CALLS

00:08:07.883 --> 00:08:09.969
Why? What is it?

00:08:11.762 --> 00:08:12.722
Mr. Heo.

00:08:13.306 --> 00:08:16.475
Brace yourself
for what I'm about to tell you.

00:08:17.268 --> 00:08:19.520
<i>You know the last scene you told me about?</i>

00:08:20.187 --> 00:08:21.897
<i>The final scene at the hospital.</i>

00:08:21.981 --> 00:08:24.984
<i>There's an even darker ending,</i>
<i>and I think it just unfolded!</i>

00:08:26.527 --> 00:08:29.322
What do you mean by a darker ending?

00:09:01.604 --> 00:09:05.149
<i>I woke up in the middle of the night</i>
<i>to find I had missed calls.</i>

00:09:05.232 --> 00:09:06.359
SE-YUN
2 MISSED CALLS

00:09:09.904 --> 00:09:12.073
<i>I had a bad feeling, so I called back.</i>

00:09:12.156 --> 00:09:15.993
<i>The person you are calling</i>
<i>is not available…</i>

00:09:26.837 --> 00:09:28.547
<i>Kang! Lee Kang!</i>

00:09:29.590 --> 00:09:31.550
<i>Kang… Kang!</i>

00:09:32.468 --> 00:09:33.594
Lee Kang.

00:09:36.430 --> 00:09:37.515
Kang.

00:09:38.724 --> 00:09:40.851
Kang, are you listening?

00:09:45.481 --> 00:09:47.817
Dad is trying to kill Mom and me.

00:09:51.529 --> 00:09:53.698
He's going to burn the place down.

00:09:55.366 --> 00:09:56.826
He's going to kill her?

00:09:57.410 --> 00:09:58.327
Eun-joo?

00:09:59.787 --> 00:10:01.414
And burn the place down?

00:10:01.497 --> 00:10:02.873
<i>The end of the message</i>

00:10:03.541 --> 00:10:05.418
<i>was truly horrifying.</i>

00:10:58.304 --> 00:11:00.014
<i>That was the last thing I heard.</i>

00:11:04.393 --> 00:11:06.645
I'm so scared, Mr. Heo.

00:11:07.980 --> 00:11:09.190
<i>What do we do now?</i>

00:11:12.735 --> 00:11:15.488
That son of a bitch has finally lost it.

00:11:15.988 --> 00:11:17.656
He's trying to bury any evidence.

00:11:19.950 --> 00:11:23.162
He's found out
that Eun-joo knows everything.

00:11:23.245 --> 00:11:24.538
<i>Please, Mr. Heo.</i>

00:11:25.039 --> 00:11:29.043
<i>I'm headed to Seoul right now,</i>
<i>but it'll take a while to get there, so</i>

00:11:29.543 --> 00:11:31.378
<i>could you head there now?</i>

00:11:32.213 --> 00:11:33.464
<i>-Find out what's--</i>
<i>-</i>Address.

00:11:33.547 --> 00:11:35.800
Just give me the address.

00:11:38.719 --> 00:11:40.095
Kim Su-hun, you bastard.

00:11:41.263 --> 00:11:43.349
Just how far are you planning to go?

00:11:45.476 --> 00:11:47.686
How far are you planning to go, damn it?

00:13:13.272 --> 00:13:14.189
Yun…

00:13:17.359 --> 00:13:18.777
Where's Yun?

00:13:29.371 --> 00:13:30.331
Tell me.

00:13:33.375 --> 00:13:34.293
Tell me

00:13:35.169 --> 00:13:37.922
that our Yun is okay.

00:13:42.468 --> 00:13:43.594
Don't tell me…

00:13:44.845 --> 00:13:46.138
Please tell me you didn't.

00:13:48.098 --> 00:13:49.308
You didn't, did you?

00:13:51.185 --> 00:13:52.269
Tell me now.

00:13:52.811 --> 00:13:53.979
Tell me now!

00:13:56.231 --> 00:13:57.316
After all this,

00:13:58.275 --> 00:14:00.486
can you still call yourself a father?

00:14:01.695 --> 00:14:04.031
How could you?

00:14:04.114 --> 00:14:05.574
Goddammit!

00:14:07.618 --> 00:14:08.994
Why'd you go and do that?

00:14:09.787 --> 00:14:12.081
Why did you have to go digging around?

00:14:14.458 --> 00:14:16.001
You were better off not knowing.

00:14:39.858 --> 00:14:41.193
If you had just ignored it…

00:14:42.069 --> 00:14:43.195
That way…

00:14:49.368 --> 00:14:52.496
we could have kept pretending to be happy!

00:15:08.345 --> 00:15:11.140
No, you son of a bitch!

00:15:12.391 --> 00:15:14.643
Kim Su-hun, you son of a bitch! No!

00:15:16.854 --> 00:15:19.690
This ending is unacceptable.

00:15:21.942 --> 00:15:23.944
Not for my Eun-joo.

00:15:25.029 --> 00:15:26.655
Not my dear Eun-joo.

00:15:27.656 --> 00:15:29.575
You bastard, I'll kill you.

00:15:36.165 --> 00:15:36.999
EMERGENCY SERVICES

00:15:53.682 --> 00:15:54.558
What the heck?

00:15:55.517 --> 00:15:56.560
Hey, get in.

00:16:06.445 --> 00:16:09.323
License plate 6904, you're speeding.
Pull over to the right.

00:16:12.034 --> 00:16:14.870
6904, pull over to the right, now!

00:16:17.039 --> 00:16:19.416
Good. This is actually for the best!

00:16:20.000 --> 00:16:21.668
Stay right behind me, okay?

00:16:21.752 --> 00:16:23.670
Follow and keep up!

00:16:23.754 --> 00:16:25.964
This is how the world
will find out about you!

00:16:26.632 --> 00:16:29.259
You're finished.
You're fucked, you bastard!

00:16:30.219 --> 00:16:32.262
License plate 6904, pull over!

00:16:36.141 --> 00:16:38.018
Is he crazy? On his tail.

00:16:38.102 --> 00:16:39.728
You got it, sir.

00:16:57.538 --> 00:16:58.664
Get out of the way.

00:17:09.091 --> 00:17:10.592
Move!

00:17:11.969 --> 00:17:12.886
Move!

00:17:18.058 --> 00:17:18.892
Should we leave?

00:17:18.976 --> 00:17:21.645
-Let's wait and see.
-All these bloody prank calls.

00:17:21.728 --> 00:17:24.106
-When did they call?
-What are you doing?

00:17:24.189 --> 00:17:26.441
Why are you still standing out here?

00:17:26.525 --> 00:17:28.944
Right, are you the one
who reported the fire?

00:17:29.027 --> 00:17:30.028
Yes, that's me.

00:17:30.529 --> 00:17:34.324
What are you waiting for?
You need to get in there now!

00:17:34.408 --> 00:17:39.037
That bastard is in there right now,
setting the damn place on fire!

00:17:39.872 --> 00:17:41.915
Hey! Kim Su-hun!

00:17:41.999 --> 00:17:43.417
Hey, you bastard!

00:17:43.500 --> 00:17:44.793
Open the door right now!

00:17:44.877 --> 00:17:46.420
Open the door! Open it!

00:17:46.503 --> 00:17:49.798
What fire are you talking about, sir?

00:17:49.882 --> 00:17:52.593
What's all this? An emergency patient?
What's going on here?

00:17:53.177 --> 00:17:56.346
Well, we're wondering the same thing.

00:17:58.223 --> 00:18:00.642
Sir, perhaps you made a mistake?

00:18:00.726 --> 00:18:02.019
A mistake?

00:18:02.519 --> 00:18:05.314
Do you people have any idea
what's going on in there?

00:18:05.397 --> 00:18:08.692
What's going on here?
Thank you for all your hard work.

00:18:08.775 --> 00:18:10.611
-Open up now, you bastard!
-Sir.

00:18:10.694 --> 00:18:14.406
Do you know how many red lights you ran?
Why didn't you stop?

00:18:14.489 --> 00:18:16.074
Good, you're here.

00:18:16.158 --> 00:18:17.868
Cops. You're the police.

00:18:17.951 --> 00:18:19.828
Hurry up and get this door open!

00:18:19.912 --> 00:18:21.997
That's not important right now!

00:18:22.080 --> 00:18:23.207
No, she's not dead yet.

00:18:23.290 --> 00:18:25.584
I have to save Eun-joo.
We have to save her!

00:18:25.667 --> 00:18:27.044
Eun-joo can't die!

00:18:27.836 --> 00:18:30.589
Come on, get this damn door open now!

00:18:31.089 --> 00:18:34.843
Do you all know the writer Kim Su-hun?
Well? Kim Su-hun, the writer?

00:18:34.927 --> 00:18:37.846
That shameless bastard
who won't stop showing up on TV.

00:18:37.930 --> 00:18:41.725
That bastard is in there right now
killing people. You hear me?

00:18:41.808 --> 00:18:44.853
People are dying in there,
you motherfuckers!

00:18:44.937 --> 00:18:47.231
Open up now! Hurry up and open the door!

00:18:47.314 --> 00:18:49.608
-Please calm down.
-Kim Su-hun, you son of a bitch!

00:18:49.691 --> 00:18:52.027
-Sir.
-We get it, so please just calm down.

00:18:52.110 --> 00:18:53.820
-Sir, please.
-Let go! It's all true!

00:18:53.904 --> 00:18:56.031
Professor? Professor Heo Mun-oh!

00:19:02.162 --> 00:19:03.997
What are you doing at my house, sir?

00:19:06.875 --> 00:19:07.709
Hey, Heo Mun-oh.

00:19:11.546 --> 00:19:12.381
Mun-oh?

00:19:18.679 --> 00:19:20.389
You're Mun-oh, right?

00:19:24.851 --> 00:19:26.853
What's all this about?

00:19:35.612 --> 00:19:36.738
Mun-oh?

00:19:39.116 --> 00:19:40.659
What's this about?

00:19:46.081 --> 00:19:47.249
Mun-oh?

00:19:48.292 --> 00:19:49.126
What's wrong?

00:20:04.725 --> 00:20:08.395
I don't know what's going on,
but why don't we step inside and…

00:21:21.927 --> 00:21:23.261
LEE KANG

00:21:24.513 --> 00:21:25.639
Answer the phone.

00:21:27.057 --> 00:21:28.809
Just pick up, you bastard.

00:21:30.310 --> 00:21:31.520
Come on, pick up.

00:21:32.104 --> 00:21:33.814
Pick up, you bastard!

00:21:34.815 --> 00:21:36.066
Answer already!

00:21:38.110 --> 00:21:40.153
Pick up the damn phone!

00:21:40.695 --> 00:21:42.823
-Son of a bitch.
<i>-The person you are calling…</i>

00:21:53.166 --> 00:21:55.669
MR. HEO MUN-OH

00:22:06.012 --> 00:22:07.097
Hey, Lee Kang!

00:22:09.057 --> 00:22:10.016
Stop right there!

00:22:12.769 --> 00:22:13.603
Hey!

00:22:14.354 --> 00:22:15.814
What the heck is wrong with you?

00:22:16.398 --> 00:22:18.233
Stop right there. We need to talk.

00:22:18.733 --> 00:22:21.570
What happened? Hey, stop right there!

00:22:22.070 --> 00:22:23.071
You little shit.

00:22:33.790 --> 00:22:34.666
Stop right there!

00:23:17.167 --> 00:23:18.710
Where did that bastard go?

00:23:55.705 --> 00:23:56.540
Honey.

00:23:57.749 --> 00:23:58.583
Why the suitcase?

00:24:11.346 --> 00:24:13.807
Was that bastard Lee Kang here?

00:24:20.355 --> 00:24:22.107
So he came by here,

00:24:23.525 --> 00:24:24.359
right?

00:24:26.069 --> 00:24:27.112
That bastard was here?

00:24:28.363 --> 00:24:29.322
What did he say?

00:24:30.031 --> 00:24:31.324
What did you two talk about?

00:24:34.869 --> 00:24:36.121
Answer me, damn it!

00:24:36.955 --> 00:24:40.166
What did that bastard tell you?

00:24:40.667 --> 00:24:43.587
That bastard is a complete nutjob!

00:24:54.556 --> 00:24:56.975
Now that I think about it,
it's a little strange.

00:24:58.143 --> 00:24:59.394
Why would he come here

00:25:00.353 --> 00:25:01.813
when I wasn't even home?

00:25:05.150 --> 00:25:06.026
You're smirking?

00:25:08.153 --> 00:25:09.821
What's with that smirk?

00:25:10.989 --> 00:25:12.324
Did you two do something?

00:25:14.492 --> 00:25:18.163
Did you get drunk and fool around
with that young bastard in broad daylight?

00:25:38.808 --> 00:25:40.143
No way.

00:25:42.312 --> 00:25:44.105
You wouldn't.

00:25:46.024 --> 00:25:48.276
He's not a kid. He's an adult.

00:25:51.154 --> 00:25:52.113
So what?

00:26:16.971 --> 00:26:19.057
How could he when he has a wife like you?

00:26:22.310 --> 00:26:24.729
Mr. Heo sure is a fool, isn't he?

00:27:03.143 --> 00:27:04.853
<i>Sure, feel free to imagine</i>

00:27:05.520 --> 00:27:07.021
what we did.

00:27:07.981 --> 00:27:09.441
That's your specialty, isn't it?

00:27:12.527 --> 00:27:13.653
"We"?

00:27:16.114 --> 00:27:17.824
Have you actually lost it?

00:27:19.576 --> 00:27:22.036
-Why, so suddenly…
-It wasn't sudden.

00:27:23.621 --> 00:27:25.373
Kang came to see me

00:27:26.124 --> 00:27:28.960
while you were obsessing
over the story about Ahn Eun-joo.

00:27:52.650 --> 00:27:53.568
I see.

00:27:56.446 --> 00:27:58.531
So that's what he's been up to all along.

00:27:59.949 --> 00:28:00.909
While deceiving me.

00:28:02.869 --> 00:28:03.995
Yes, truthfully…

00:28:06.414 --> 00:28:08.291
what we did wasn't really lessons.

00:28:10.168 --> 00:28:13.588
Mr. Heo covets stories
and gets swept up in them quickly…

00:28:16.299 --> 00:28:18.635
but he doesn't know
which stories truly matter.

00:28:24.641 --> 00:28:27.519
What's more,
you don't exist in his stories.

00:28:30.605 --> 00:28:31.940
Yeah, I know.

00:28:34.651 --> 00:28:35.944
The truth is,

00:28:37.737 --> 00:28:39.781
I've known for a long time.

00:28:46.746 --> 00:28:47.956
But why are you…

00:28:50.250 --> 00:28:52.252
telling me all this?

00:29:00.009 --> 00:29:00.969
I'll tell you that…

00:29:04.305 --> 00:29:05.223
next time.

00:29:07.225 --> 00:29:09.352
<i>We met a few more times after that</i>

00:29:10.311 --> 00:29:12.021
<i>and became friends.</i>

00:29:13.147 --> 00:29:17.193
What the fuck is this bullshit?

00:29:21.155 --> 00:29:22.073
Did you sleep with him?

00:29:26.828 --> 00:29:28.329
Is that important right now?

00:29:28.913 --> 00:29:30.623
Is that all you care about?

00:29:32.500 --> 00:29:33.835
Kang was right.

00:29:34.335 --> 00:29:36.379
Even now, you don't know what to ask.

00:29:36.462 --> 00:29:38.548
You have no idea what's truly important.

00:29:39.757 --> 00:29:42.051
Then what's important right now? Tell me.

00:29:42.719 --> 00:29:43.761
No, I won't.

00:29:44.262 --> 00:29:46.723
Because we're nothing to each other now.

00:29:49.309 --> 00:29:50.560
What did you say?

00:29:51.436 --> 00:29:52.562
Don't you get it?

00:29:53.062 --> 00:29:54.981
I won't live with you anymore.

00:29:56.024 --> 00:29:58.234
I won't put up with you anymore.

00:30:00.945 --> 00:30:04.157
I'm going to start writing
my own story now.

00:30:15.043 --> 00:30:15.960
Jo Hyeon-suk.

00:30:19.923 --> 00:30:21.215
Jo Hyeon-suk.

00:30:24.510 --> 00:30:25.845
Hyeon-suk!

00:30:45.323 --> 00:30:46.866
Hyeon-suk, don't go.

00:30:49.494 --> 00:30:51.412
Please don't go, Jo Hyeon-suk.

00:30:54.040 --> 00:30:55.249
Don't go.

00:31:03.049 --> 00:31:04.175
What the heck…

00:31:06.135 --> 00:31:07.428
What is this?

00:31:11.015 --> 00:31:11.933
What…

00:31:21.401 --> 00:31:22.235
Yeah?

00:31:22.318 --> 00:31:25.238
<i>Mun-oh, something terrible has happened!</i>

00:31:25.321 --> 00:31:27.073
Have you seen the school forum?

00:31:27.573 --> 00:31:28.741
It's blowing up.

00:31:30.493 --> 00:31:31.828
What about the forum?

00:31:33.121 --> 00:31:34.080
Just tell me.

00:31:35.039 --> 00:31:38.251
<i>Well, I don't know how to explain it…</i>

00:31:40.253 --> 00:31:42.463
Come on, what are you trying to say?

00:31:43.464 --> 00:31:44.674
Just read it to me.

00:31:45.883 --> 00:31:48.803
Okay, then.
I'll just read you a few sentences.

00:31:49.721 --> 00:31:54.100
"Professor Heo Mun-oh forced me
to write defamatory content

00:31:54.183 --> 00:31:56.060
<i>about the author Kim Su-hun."</i>

00:31:57.478 --> 00:31:58.813
<i>"Blinded by jealousy,</i>

00:31:58.896 --> 00:32:02.483
<i>he fabricated false information</i>
<i>with the intention</i>

00:32:02.567 --> 00:32:04.986
of destroying Kim Su-hun's reputation."

00:32:06.112 --> 00:32:09.907
"Once I caught on to his intentions,
he tried to bribe me by offering

00:32:09.991 --> 00:32:14.537
to slip me the problems
of the programming competition in return."

00:32:14.620 --> 00:32:16.956
<i>"When I refused to be coerced any longer,</i>

00:32:17.540 --> 00:32:19.917
he even stole my work
and claimed it as his own…"

00:32:20.001 --> 00:32:23.379
<i>Well, anyway, that's the gist of it.</i>

00:32:23.463 --> 00:32:25.256
<i>It was posted anonymously,</i>

00:32:25.339 --> 00:32:28.760
and they even warned that they'd upload
that novel as evidence soon.

00:32:28.843 --> 00:32:30.011
The thing is,

00:32:30.511 --> 00:32:32.680
the view count keeps… It's skyrocketing.

00:32:33.973 --> 00:32:35.975
And people keep posting comments.

00:32:36.476 --> 00:32:37.351
Mun-oh.

00:32:38.019 --> 00:32:40.354
What's all this about?
It's not true, is it?

00:32:52.742 --> 00:32:53.576
My novel.

00:32:54.702 --> 00:32:56.120
Where's my novel?

00:32:56.662 --> 00:32:58.039
Where did my novel go?

00:33:00.875 --> 00:33:02.210
Where did my novel go?

00:33:03.503 --> 00:33:04.420
My novel.

00:33:05.379 --> 00:33:07.799
Where did my novel go? My novel.

00:33:10.426 --> 00:33:13.721
Lee Kang, you bastard. You took my novel?

00:33:14.222 --> 00:33:15.640
How dare you touch my novel.

00:33:16.140 --> 00:33:18.976
<i>The number you have dialed</i>
<i>is not in service.</i>

00:33:19.060 --> 00:33:21.312
-What?
<i>-Please check and try again.</i>

00:33:21.395 --> 00:33:22.939
You son of a bitch.

00:33:25.608 --> 00:33:28.486
<i>The number you have dialed</i>
<i>is not in service.</i>

00:33:28.569 --> 00:33:30.279
You son of a bitch!

00:33:30.363 --> 00:33:33.199
You motherfucker!
You little son of a bitch!

00:33:33.282 --> 00:33:35.618
You son of a bitch!

00:33:36.369 --> 00:33:37.453
You took my novel…

00:33:37.537 --> 00:33:41.040
You can't! You son of a bitch. No.

00:33:41.124 --> 00:33:42.875
You son of a bitch!

00:33:45.002 --> 00:33:45.878
Lee Kang.

00:33:46.921 --> 00:33:48.297
That son of a bitch!

00:33:49.549 --> 00:33:50.925
Why would you…

00:33:52.510 --> 00:33:54.303
Why did you do this to me?

00:33:54.804 --> 00:33:56.472
Why me?

00:33:56.973 --> 00:33:59.308
<i>Last week,</i>
<i>we reported on shocking allegations</i>

00:33:59.392 --> 00:34:03.187
<i>about a professor</i>
<i>at a prestigious university in Seoul.</i>

00:34:03.271 --> 00:34:06.149
<i>-</i>That's him, right?
-<i>A post on the online forum claimed</i>

00:34:06.232 --> 00:34:10.528
<i>that he forced a student to write a novel</i>
<i>slandering renowned author Kim Su-hun.</i>

00:34:11.320 --> 00:34:15.449
<i>Today, the full novel was posted online</i>
<i>along with the professor's identity,</i>

00:34:15.533 --> 00:34:17.660
<i>causing an even bigger uproar.</i>

00:34:18.161 --> 00:34:21.164
<i>What's even more shocking about this novel</i>

00:34:21.247 --> 00:34:25.501
<i>is that it consistently depicts Kim Su-hun</i>
<i>as a bloodthirsty, psychopathic criminal.</i>

00:34:28.004 --> 00:34:31.299
He can't even write his own work,
yet he slanders another writer.

00:34:50.443 --> 00:34:53.237
TRASH BELONGS IN THE TRASH CAN!

00:35:02.705 --> 00:35:05.917
<i>In response,</i>
<i>Kim Su-hun's legal representative stated</i>

00:35:06.000 --> 00:35:07.877
<i>that they are preparing a lawsuit,</i>

00:35:07.960 --> 00:35:10.463
<i>as it amounts to deliberate</i>
<i>and serious defamation.</i>

00:35:11.464 --> 00:35:13.132
<i>Meanwhile, the school in question</i>

00:35:13.216 --> 00:35:16.052
<i>has decided to convene</i>
<i>the disciplinary committee.</i>

00:35:16.135 --> 00:35:20.264
<i>Public attention is focused on</i>
<i>how they will handle this situation.</i>

00:35:37.782 --> 00:35:40.201
You were deceived by a student?

00:35:43.454 --> 00:35:45.790
You honestly expect us to believe that?

00:35:47.625 --> 00:35:50.127
Do you think
you can resolve this situation

00:35:50.211 --> 00:35:52.964
with this statement
full of pathetic excuses?

00:35:56.634 --> 00:36:01.097
How will you take responsibility
for our school's damaged reputation?

00:36:01.180 --> 00:36:03.224
It's humiliating.

00:36:03.307 --> 00:36:06.560
Our school is plastered all over
the news and YouTube every day…

00:36:09.313 --> 00:36:14.068
Your recent teaching record shows
you've been canceling a lot of classes

00:36:14.610 --> 00:36:16.153
and skipping faculty meetings.

00:36:17.029 --> 00:36:19.365
But the most serious issue here

00:36:19.865 --> 00:36:22.535
is you leaking the programming competition
test problems.

00:36:23.953 --> 00:36:25.538
This is outrageous.

00:36:26.414 --> 00:36:30.251
This isn't a matter of
whether you're fit to teach. It's a crime!

00:36:32.503 --> 00:36:33.546
Professor.

00:36:34.130 --> 00:36:35.756
Look here, Professor Heo Mun-oh.

00:36:38.968 --> 00:36:40.469
A confrontation? Please.

00:36:41.846 --> 00:36:44.390
Lee Kang is currently
on a leave of absence,

00:36:44.473 --> 00:36:47.018
and you said
you don't even have his number.

00:36:55.776 --> 00:36:56.610
Fine.

00:36:58.029 --> 00:37:03.159
Let's say you were indeed
completely deceived by Lee Kang.

00:37:04.327 --> 00:37:05.995
If that's true,

00:37:06.704 --> 00:37:07.872
why do you think

00:37:08.873 --> 00:37:10.583
that student did this?

00:37:29.143 --> 00:37:30.353
I don't know.

00:37:37.818 --> 00:37:39.737
I don't know why…

00:37:46.535 --> 00:37:48.287
he did this to me either.

00:39:03.946 --> 00:39:07.283
You bastard, stop calling me.
Wrong fucking number!

00:40:41.544 --> 00:40:43.629
<i>It's been a while, Mr. Heo.</i>

00:40:44.171 --> 00:40:45.047
<i>This is Lee Kang.</i>

00:40:46.423 --> 00:40:48.259
<i>I sent you an email. Please check.</i>

00:40:48.342 --> 00:40:50.094
You son of a bitch.

00:40:50.970 --> 00:40:53.681
That fucking bastard reached out?

00:41:14.118 --> 00:41:16.537
MR. HEO, HERE IS MY LAST ASSIGNMENT

00:41:17.788 --> 00:41:19.123
<i>Mr. Heo.</i>

00:41:19.957 --> 00:41:21.542
<i>Have you been well</i>?

00:41:22.501 --> 00:41:25.087
<i>I hear you've been</i>
<i>desperately looking for me.</i>

00:41:25.588 --> 00:41:28.549
<i>I get it.</i>
<i>You must have a lot of questions.</i>

00:41:29.258 --> 00:41:33.387
<i>I'm writing this now</i>
<i>to repay you for your patience.</i>

00:41:34.054 --> 00:41:37.558
<i>I'd say…</i>
<i>this is my final writing assignment.</i>

00:41:39.768 --> 00:41:41.520
<i>Do you remember that day,</i>

00:41:42.479 --> 00:41:44.315
<i>twelve years ago?</i>

00:41:46.150 --> 00:41:47.484
<i>Twelve years ago?</i>

00:42:05.127 --> 00:42:07.129
Are you going to keep sulking like that?

00:42:07.630 --> 00:42:08.714
We're almost there.

00:42:08.797 --> 00:42:10.591
You could've just gone by yourself.

00:42:11.717 --> 00:42:13.636
Why do you have to bother me like this?

00:42:14.219 --> 00:42:15.888
Bother you?

00:42:16.388 --> 00:42:19.224
I thought a change of scenery
might do you good.

00:42:20.392 --> 00:42:23.354
You've been frustrated lately,
since progress has been slow.

00:42:24.605 --> 00:42:29.276
If you get out and move around a little,
it might help with writer's block.

00:42:35.491 --> 00:42:37.493
Looks like we're almost at the orphanage.

00:42:37.576 --> 00:42:38.410
And

00:42:39.036 --> 00:42:40.871
what am I even supposed to do there?

00:42:40.954 --> 00:42:42.665
You don't have to do anything.

00:42:42.748 --> 00:42:45.751
Just go for a walk or read a book
while I'm working.

00:42:46.251 --> 00:42:48.253
Let's go eat
something delicious afterward.

00:42:56.387 --> 00:42:57.513
What is it?

00:42:58.555 --> 00:42:59.765
What's wrong?

00:43:10.275 --> 00:43:12.486
NEW DRIVER

00:43:17.825 --> 00:43:19.618
Honey, could you step outside?

00:43:34.842 --> 00:43:37.553
Why weren't you paying attention
to the road?

00:43:37.636 --> 00:43:38.929
What should we do?

00:43:41.390 --> 00:43:42.599
Did we get a flat?

00:43:48.397 --> 00:43:52.818
If one of your friends gives an answer
and you also have it,

00:43:53.318 --> 00:43:57.114
you can add a "me too" sticker.

00:43:57.197 --> 00:43:59.700
And when you complete a bingo line,

00:43:59.783 --> 00:44:01.744
you shout "Bingo!"

00:44:01.827 --> 00:44:04.580
Bingo!

00:44:04.663 --> 00:44:08.375
So, for example,
what's your favorite fruit?

00:44:08.459 --> 00:44:09.460
-Lame.
-Watermelon.

00:44:09.543 --> 00:44:10.878
Watermelon? Then…

00:44:12.212 --> 00:44:13.589
This is boring.

00:44:17.050 --> 00:44:17.885
Miss?

00:44:18.635 --> 00:44:19.470
Yes?

00:44:19.970 --> 00:44:22.014
Do I have to do this?

00:44:23.515 --> 00:44:25.601
I guess you don't have to.

00:44:26.560 --> 00:44:30.397
If you don't want to,
you can just watch the others.

00:44:31.273 --> 00:44:32.107
Okay?

00:45:24.576 --> 00:45:25.410
How old are you?

00:45:27.371 --> 00:45:29.998
Why do adults always ask
that sort of thing?

00:45:31.416 --> 00:45:32.918
How old are <i>you</i>, mister?

00:45:37.422 --> 00:45:40.008
Please tell me. How old are you?

00:45:42.010 --> 00:45:43.512
I'm eight.

00:45:47.224 --> 00:45:48.684
Earlier, why didn't you

00:45:50.060 --> 00:45:51.311
want to get counseling?

00:45:54.898 --> 00:45:56.316
Was it really too lame?

00:45:57.776 --> 00:46:00.571
They always ask me to talk about
my mom and dad anyway.

00:46:02.948 --> 00:46:04.157
It's annoying.

00:46:07.703 --> 00:46:10.539
Talk about your mom and dad? Like what?

00:46:10.622 --> 00:46:12.374
I said I won't talk about them.

00:46:15.127 --> 00:46:17.379
If I talk about them to just anyone,

00:46:17.880 --> 00:46:19.840
Mom and Dad would be sad.

00:46:27.389 --> 00:46:28.557
Is that so?

00:46:32.352 --> 00:46:33.478
Then,

00:46:34.229 --> 00:46:36.857
instead of talking about your mom and dad…

00:46:39.026 --> 00:46:41.820
Stand up. You can't see them
from down here.

00:46:43.739 --> 00:46:46.366
There. Do you see those ducks over there?

00:46:47.951 --> 00:46:49.328
How about

00:46:50.037 --> 00:46:51.705
we talk about those ducks?

00:46:52.831 --> 00:46:54.666
-Ducks?
-Yeah, ducks.

00:46:56.376 --> 00:46:57.336
Okay, watch.

00:46:57.419 --> 00:47:01.298
Do you see that tiny baby duck over there?

00:47:01.798 --> 00:47:02.841
You see it?

00:47:04.134 --> 00:47:05.469
That's you.

00:47:06.428 --> 00:47:10.057
And you see that bigger duck
in front of it?

00:47:10.557 --> 00:47:12.100
That bigger duck is your mom.

00:47:13.352 --> 00:47:16.563
And the duck next to her is your dad.

00:47:18.565 --> 00:47:19.608
And so,

00:47:20.525 --> 00:47:23.111
we try talking about the duck family.

00:47:24.363 --> 00:47:25.405
That

00:47:26.698 --> 00:47:28.283
is called a story.

00:47:30.035 --> 00:47:31.078
A story?

00:47:31.161 --> 00:47:32.037
Yeah, a story.

00:47:35.290 --> 00:47:36.208
Why

00:47:36.792 --> 00:47:38.418
was that baby duck

00:47:39.044 --> 00:47:42.005
so annoyed earlier?

00:47:44.758 --> 00:47:46.009
And

00:47:47.678 --> 00:47:49.846
why is he so angry now?

00:48:06.196 --> 00:48:07.906
Because he misses them.

00:48:11.868 --> 00:48:13.412
The mom duck.

00:48:17.332 --> 00:48:18.834
The dad duck.

00:48:22.504 --> 00:48:23.463
Every day.

00:48:26.675 --> 00:48:27.968
Because…

00:48:31.847 --> 00:48:34.808
he misses them every night.

00:48:37.894 --> 00:48:39.855
<i>Thanks to him, the little boy</i>

00:48:40.564 --> 00:48:42.190
<i>learned what stories were.</i>

00:48:42.691 --> 00:48:44.484
<i>Thanks to the duck family story,</i>

00:48:44.568 --> 00:48:46.903
<i>he was able to open up</i>
<i>about his mom and dad</i>

00:48:46.987 --> 00:48:49.364
<i>after holding it in for so long.</i>

00:48:53.869 --> 00:48:55.495
The dad duck

00:48:56.663 --> 00:48:58.373
was really strong.

00:48:58.874 --> 00:49:01.626
<i>The little boy cherished that moment.</i>

00:49:02.210 --> 00:49:05.338
<i>He felt like he was truly opening up</i>
<i>without any defiance or resistance</i>

00:49:05.422 --> 00:49:09.801
<i>for the first time</i>
<i>since coming to the orphanage.</i>

00:49:11.970 --> 00:49:13.221
And where did they go?

00:49:15.140 --> 00:49:18.226
The dad duck had a truck.

00:49:18.310 --> 00:49:20.645
When the baby duck laughed,

00:49:21.563 --> 00:49:23.565
the mom duck would laugh along.

00:49:25.025 --> 00:49:28.945
The baby duck was really happy.

00:49:31.615 --> 00:49:34.618
Thank you so much for coming all this way.

00:49:35.243 --> 00:49:36.661
Don't mention it.

00:49:36.745 --> 00:49:39.414
I needed to do it for my practicum anyway.

00:49:39.915 --> 00:49:44.252
I'm the one who should be thanking you
for reaching out to me first.

00:49:53.303 --> 00:49:55.138
I'll be going, then.

00:49:55.222 --> 00:49:56.640
Have a safe trip back.

00:49:56.723 --> 00:49:58.642
-Thank you.
-Thank you for coming.

00:50:02.896 --> 00:50:04.314
Miss?

00:50:05.482 --> 00:50:07.692
Oh, it's you.

00:50:08.318 --> 00:50:09.694
Where's the male teacher?

00:50:10.695 --> 00:50:13.115
Male teacher? Oh!

00:50:14.699 --> 00:50:17.828
Well, he should be around here somewhere.

00:50:20.080 --> 00:50:21.623
Why do you ask?

00:50:35.679 --> 00:50:37.347
What's gotten into you?

00:50:44.104 --> 00:50:45.981
Something peculiar happened just now.

00:50:46.481 --> 00:50:49.067
You know that boy
you were talking to earlier?

00:50:49.151 --> 00:50:51.403
I saw the two of you talking.

00:50:51.903 --> 00:50:53.655
He came up to me just now

00:50:54.156 --> 00:50:56.950
and asked me for your address,

00:50:57.033 --> 00:50:58.869
saying he wanted to write to you.

00:50:58.952 --> 00:51:01.872
I guess he really enjoyed talking to you.

00:51:01.955 --> 00:51:03.707
It made <i>me </i>proud.

00:51:03.790 --> 00:51:05.500
What did you two talk about?

00:51:06.042 --> 00:51:07.460
And did you give it to him?

00:51:07.961 --> 00:51:09.796
Of course I did. Isn't he adorable?

00:51:09.880 --> 00:51:11.631
His name is Lee Kang.

00:51:11.715 --> 00:51:14.885
Why did you give it to him? What a hassle!

00:51:15.385 --> 00:51:17.262
I thought you two had a fun chat.

00:51:17.345 --> 00:51:18.972
What do you mean "fun"?

00:51:19.055 --> 00:51:21.516
I was just hearing him out
because he was talking.

00:51:21.600 --> 00:51:24.394
I asked him to see
if I could get inspired,

00:51:25.145 --> 00:51:29.566
but his parents died
in a truck accident or something.

00:51:29.649 --> 00:51:32.652
Anyway, it's the same old sob story.
Nothing new.

00:51:34.821 --> 00:51:37.073
What do you mean "nothing new"?

00:51:37.574 --> 00:51:39.242
How can you call it a sob story?

00:51:39.743 --> 00:51:42.204
Of course the kids here
have been through a lot.

00:51:42.287 --> 00:51:44.080
Yeah, and so what?

00:51:44.581 --> 00:51:46.917
A story still has to be riveting.

00:51:47.000 --> 00:51:49.878
It needs a special something
to make it a story.

00:51:50.921 --> 00:51:53.131
Anyway, forget it. Let's go.

00:51:53.215 --> 00:51:56.009
If he writes to me,
I'll cut him off on my end.

00:51:56.509 --> 00:51:59.095
Hurry up. Hand me the keys. I'll drive.

00:52:18.573 --> 00:52:20.492
YEONSEO UNIVERSITY
PROFESSOR HEO MUN-OH

00:52:35.006 --> 00:52:36.967
WELCOME, FRESHMEN OF YEONSEO UNIVERSITY

00:52:52.732 --> 00:52:55.527
PROFESSOR'S OFFICE, HEO MUN-OH

00:52:56.152 --> 00:52:59.364
Where's the department office?
Maybe it's on a different floor?

00:52:59.990 --> 00:53:01.116
Let's go over there.

00:53:02.367 --> 00:53:03.743
Oh? Heo Mun-oh?

00:53:05.203 --> 00:53:08.206
I signed up for his class this semester.
Basic Composition.

00:53:08.290 --> 00:53:11.668
I heard you should steer clear of him.
That his classes are hard.

00:53:11.751 --> 00:53:14.754
Guess what? Professor Heo Mun-oh
went to college with my dad.

00:53:14.838 --> 00:53:15.922
Wanna know the kicker?

00:53:16.423 --> 00:53:19.259
He had the hugest crush on my mom
when they were students.

00:53:19.759 --> 00:53:23.013
And he used to get jealous of my dad
during composition class.

00:53:23.096 --> 00:53:25.557
I overheard my parents
talking about it once.

00:53:27.058 --> 00:53:29.227
He had a crush on your mom? Small world.

00:53:50.206 --> 00:53:53.543
Are you in YDOC too?
They gave these as freshmen goodies.

00:53:57.172 --> 00:54:00.383
I'm Kim Se-yun, class of '25.
Library and Information Science. You?

00:54:00.467 --> 00:54:02.635
Lee Kang, class of '25.
Electronics Engineering.

00:54:25.200 --> 00:54:28.787
Yun. Kids? Come and have some snacks.

00:54:37.295 --> 00:54:38.588
-Eat up, kids.
-Wow.

00:54:38.671 --> 00:54:40.382
-Thank you for the food!
-Thank you.

00:54:40.465 --> 00:54:41.508
-Looks good.
-Enjoy.

00:54:41.591 --> 00:54:42.592
<i>The truth is,</i>

00:54:44.135 --> 00:54:46.096
<i>there never was a housekeeper.</i>

00:54:47.305 --> 00:54:49.099
Our lessons are over.

00:54:49.599 --> 00:54:50.725
Over!

00:54:54.437 --> 00:54:55.522
What the…

00:54:55.605 --> 00:54:56.523
Oh my God!

00:54:58.483 --> 00:55:00.360
-Oh my God!
-Was there an accident?

00:55:04.989 --> 00:55:06.866
Oh no, she's bleeding. Hurry!

00:55:06.950 --> 00:55:09.244
<i>That's when I remembered what you said.</i>

00:55:11.663 --> 00:55:13.915
<i>That for a story to be a story,</i>

00:55:15.792 --> 00:55:18.336
<i>it needs a special something.</i>

00:55:20.505 --> 00:55:21.798
That's her.

00:55:25.260 --> 00:55:26.177
Min-hui.

00:55:28.138 --> 00:55:29.097
What did you say?

00:55:29.681 --> 00:55:30.515
That's Mr. Kim.

00:55:31.307 --> 00:55:32.976
Where?

00:55:46.322 --> 00:55:47.407
That man is…

00:55:49.200 --> 00:55:50.410
Mr. Kim?

00:55:52.036 --> 00:55:53.329
Se-yun's dad?

00:56:03.465 --> 00:56:04.591
<i>The accident…</i>

00:56:06.676 --> 00:56:08.511
<i>was an unforeseen coincidence.</i>

00:56:09.137 --> 00:56:10.054
Mr. Kim!

00:56:10.555 --> 00:56:12.015
-President Choi.
-Ma'am!

00:56:12.098 --> 00:56:13.683
-There.
-Right.

00:56:13.766 --> 00:56:16.269
-What do we do?
-She works for our publishing house!

00:56:16.936 --> 00:56:20.106
-Yes, I'll go with her.
-Oh, how awful!

00:56:41.252 --> 00:56:42.253
Welcome--

00:56:44.839 --> 00:56:45.715
Mr. Heo.

00:56:47.133 --> 00:56:50.637
And what's more,
that unfortunate incident happened.

00:56:51.137 --> 00:56:54.307
But for the sake of your studies,

00:56:54.891 --> 00:56:57.519
I think it'd only be my duty as a teacher…

00:56:57.602 --> 00:57:00.688
<i>From that point on,</i>
<i>the writer of this story</i>

00:57:01.189 --> 00:57:02.398
<i>was always you.</i>

00:57:05.985 --> 00:57:07.278
Kid.

00:57:08.071 --> 00:57:10.073
Why do you look so troubled these days?

00:57:10.740 --> 00:57:13.326
Is something worrying you?

00:57:16.371 --> 00:57:18.373
I just have something to do.

00:57:19.415 --> 00:57:20.875
But it's almost done.

00:57:21.876 --> 00:57:23.836
Is your part-time job wearing you down?

00:57:24.671 --> 00:57:26.047
If so, kid,

00:57:26.548 --> 00:57:28.675
don't feel like you have to visit.

00:57:29.676 --> 00:57:31.678
Why do you keep coming?

00:57:33.972 --> 00:57:36.391
If you don't want to see me,
get better already.

00:57:37.850 --> 00:57:39.102
Because to me, Director,

00:57:40.645 --> 00:57:42.480
you're both parents.

00:57:42.981 --> 00:57:44.315
My mom and dad.

00:57:44.399 --> 00:57:46.985
For goodness' sake, kiddo.

00:57:48.152 --> 00:57:52.115
I quit being the director
of the orphanage ages ago.

00:58:07.922 --> 00:58:08.840
<i>And so…</i>

00:58:10.758 --> 00:58:13.261
<i>how is your story?</i>

00:58:14.470 --> 00:58:15.513
<i>You punk!</i>

00:58:15.597 --> 00:58:17.974
<i>You listen to me carefully.</i>
<i>This isn't fabrication.</i>

00:58:18.057 --> 00:58:20.977
<i>This is the truth.</i>
<i>An undeniable truth based on all we know.</i>

00:58:33.364 --> 00:58:36.284
NOTES FROM THE LAST ROW
BY HEO MUN-OH

00:58:41.164 --> 00:58:42.665
<i>This is my novel.</i>

00:58:45.043 --> 00:58:46.002
<i>This is mine.</i>

00:58:47.253 --> 00:58:48.755
<i>My second novel.</i>

00:58:57.513 --> 00:58:58.598
<i>So…</i>

00:59:00.892 --> 00:59:03.311
<i>how is your story?</i>

00:59:08.941 --> 00:59:10.485
<i>Is your story</i>

00:59:11.986 --> 00:59:13.279
<i>special?</i>

00:59:25.333 --> 00:59:26.417
Unreal.

00:59:28.920 --> 00:59:29.754
Unreal.

00:59:35.927 --> 00:59:37.053
Unreal.

01:00:24.767 --> 01:00:25.810
So that was it?

01:00:32.066 --> 01:00:33.693
It was all because of that?

01:00:39.699 --> 01:00:41.033
That was it?

01:01:05.224 --> 01:01:07.810
Damn you!

01:01:07.894 --> 01:01:08.936
Son of a bitch.

01:01:38.508 --> 01:01:40.009
<i>Has your story</i>

01:01:40.510 --> 01:01:41.594
<i>finally become</i>

01:01:43.429 --> 01:01:45.014
<i>special?</i>

01:03:12.476 --> 01:03:13.769
<i>Faust.</i>

01:03:14.270 --> 01:03:17.398
So there are still folks
who read classics like this.

01:03:18.858 --> 01:03:22.028
It's even more of a fun read
if you know how it was written.

01:03:23.362 --> 01:03:24.530
That'll be 13,000 won.

01:03:28.034 --> 01:03:29.285
I already know.

01:03:32.371 --> 01:03:34.290
For over 60 years,

01:03:35.416 --> 01:03:37.543
it was constantly added to and revised.

01:04:23.673 --> 01:04:24.757
I'd like to resume

01:04:26.050 --> 01:04:27.301
our literature lessons.

01:04:33.432 --> 01:04:35.768
I now have a story I really want to write.

01:05:07.758 --> 01:05:08.843
What story?

01:05:23.566 --> 01:05:25.651
<i>To be continued..</i>

01:05:26.152 --> 01:05:29.155
NOTES FROM THE LAST ROW

01:07:55.217 --> 01:08:00.222
Subtitle translation by: Jimin Choi